<br>
The quoted officials were from the International Atomic Energy Agency and The USDept of Energy (whose largest line item in the budget and prime responsibilty is atomic bombs)<br>
<br>
Buried in the article are these quotes:<br>
<br>
&quot;But while nuclear supporters can see encouraging signs, the general mood has not yet swung in favour of atomic energy.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Europe remains traumatised by the Chernobyl nuclear disaster in Ukraine&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nuclear power is banned in Austria, Denmark, Greece, Ireland and Norway. Germany, Sweden and Belgium have decided to progressively close their nuclear plants.&quot;<br>
<br>
BTW - Sweden re-elected the government that promotes the ban, and so did Germany - with the highest Green vote ever recorded.<br>
<br>
Nothing has changed in slightest. The industry is in complete collapse and the players are going belly-up.<br>
<br>
A trickle of orders from very specific locations are all there is.<br>
<br>
This conference was a popped balloon of hot-air from politicions, agencies, and industries wanting a massive CPR bailout.<br>
<br>
It is actually rather sad to see poor DOE Secr. Spencer Abraham having to promote and defend positions he powerfully opposed as a Senator.<br>
